 homeschooling*\n| [[Education in Albania|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www-gewi.kfunigraz.ac.at/csbsc/country_reports/Education_Albania.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20090710034211/http://www-gewi.kfunigraz.ac.at/csbsc/country_reports/Education_Albania.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=10 July 2009|title=Education in Albania|date=10 July 2009}}</ref>\n|-\n| Andorra\n| Illegal, public education is mandatory without known exceptions.\n| Virtually no homeschooling*\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.nationsencyclopedia.com/Europe/Andorra-EDUCATION.html|title=Education - Andorra|author=|date=|website=www.nationsencyclopedia.com}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.studycountry.com/|title=The Education System in Andorra|author=|date=|website=Studycountry}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[#Austria|Austria]]\n| Legal under restrictive conditions, homeschooling is allowed as long as the instruction is at least equal to that of the state school.\n| 2100\n| [[Education in Austria|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bildungssystem.at/index.php|title=www.bildungssystem.at - Das \u00f6sterreichische Bildungssystem|author=|date=|website=www.bildungssystem.at}}</ref>{{dead link|date=November 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://diepresse.com/home/bildung/schule/pflichtschulen/710722/Haeuslicher-Unterricht-in-Oesterreich-aeusserst-selten|title=H\u00e4uslicher Unterricht in \u00d6sterreich \u00e4u\u00dferst selten|author=|date=22 November 2011|website=Die Presse}}</ref>\n|-\n| Azerbaijan\n| Illegal, public education is mandatory without known exceptions.\n| Virtually no homeschooling*\n| [[Education in Azerbaijan|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref name=\"countrystudies.us\"/>\n|-\n| Belarus\n| Illegal, public education is mandatory without known exceptions.\n| Virtually no homeschooling*\n| [[Education in Belarus|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.belarus.by/en/about-belarus/education|title=Education, Belarus - Belarus.by|author=|date=|website=www.belarus.by}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[#Belgium|Belgium]]\n| Legal under restrictive conditions, Homeschooling is a constitutional right in Belgium.\n| 500\n| [[Education in Belgium|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://onderwijs.vlaanderen.be/|title=Home|author=|date=|website=onderwijs.vlaanderen.be}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.brusselsjournal.com/node/1121|title=Crackdown on Homeschoolers: It\u2019s the UN Wot Done It - The Brussels Journal|author=|date=|website=www.brusselsjournal.com}}</ref>\n|-\n| Bosnia and Herzegovina\n| Illegal, public education is mandatory without known exceptions.\n| Virtually no homeschooling*\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.britishcouncil.org/eumd-information-background-bosnia.htm|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110606195218/http://www.britishcouncil.org/eumd-information-background-bosnia.htm|url-status=dead|archive-date=6 June 2011|title=Bosnia and Herzegovina education market introduction - Education UK Marketing - British Council|date=6 June 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.seerecon.org/bosnia/documents/education_report.pdf|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070711183930/http://www.seerecon.org/bosnia/documents/education_report.pdf|url-status=dead|archive-date=11 July 2007|title=Wayback Machine|date=11 July 2007}}</ref>\n|-\n| Bulgaria\n| Illegal, public education is mandatory. Only children with special needs may be homeschooled under strict government control.\n|fewer than 100 families\n| [[Education in Bulgaria|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.britannica.com/place/Bulgaria|title=Bulgaria - history - geography|author=|date=|website=Encyclopedia Britannica}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://hslda.org/content/hs/international/Bulgaria/default.asp|title=HSLDA - Home Schooling - Bulgaria|a