tem. Inspections are mandatory every year unless special agreements are made. also the inspections are controlled by the local district public school and not a third part inspector.\n|349-375 children (2017)\n| [[Education in Denmark|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.xn--frilring-m0a.dk/viden/hjemmeunderviste-b%C3%B8rn-i-danske-kommuner-2017|title=Homeschooled children in Denmark - statistics|website=www.fril\u00e6ring.dk}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[#Estonia|Estonia]]\n| Legal under control of school. Every homeschooled child must be supervised by an authorized school (can be a private school) and pass annual exams. Homeschooled children receive diploma from supervising school.\n| fewer than 100\n| [[Education in Estonia|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://esis.ee/|title=Domains and trademarks|author=|date=|website=esis.ee}}</ref>\n|-\n| [[#Finland|Finland]]\n| Legal as alternative to the mandatory public school system. Written and oral examinations to check on progress are mandatory.\n| 400\u2013600\n| <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oph.fi/english/page.asp?path=447,4699,4847|title=Finnish National Agency for Education - Front page|author=|date=|website=www.oph.fi|access-date=2019-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181211120830/https://www.oph.fi/english/page.asp?path=447,4699,4847|archive-date=2018-12-11|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.edu.fi/pageLast.asp?path=498,1329,1344,81146|title=Edu.fi - Opettajan verkkopalvelu|author=|date=|website=www.edu.fi|access-date=2019-02-06|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190207020737/https://www.edu.fi/pageLast.asp?path=498,1329,1344,81146|archive-date=2019-02-07|url-status=dead}}</ref>[[Education in Finland|WP]]{{Circular reference|date=February 2019}}<ref name=\"auto\">Hem och skola 4/2011 p. 7 (Swedish)</ref>\n|-\n| [[#France|France]]\n| Legal as alternative to the mandatory public school system. Inspections are man